div.p:
Dr. Wintringham directs Emetics and Purgatives to be repeated occaſionally, in order to clear the Primae Viae of their Crudities;

but I abſtain from ſuch Remedies, for they occaſion a Tumult in the nervous Juices, draw off the more fluid Parts, and deſtroy their expulſive PowerHerm. Boerhaave Aph. 1271.
               , whereby the natural Secretions are much hindred.
